The implementation is straightforward. `ring_buf_size_get` returns the amount of data available to read, calculated as `put.head - get.tail` — the difference between what's been written and what's been consumed. This is consistent with:

- `ring_buf_space_get` (free space) = `buf->size - (buf->put.head - buf->get.tail)`
- `ring_buf_is_empty` (no data) = `buf->get.head == buf->put.tail`

The function is already used at line 388 in `ring_buf_get_claim` which passes a `const struct ring_buf *`, matching the declaration.


============================================================
=== Diff ===
============================================================
--- include/zephyr/sys/ring_buffer.h
+++ include/zephyr/sys/ring_buffer.h
@@ -272,7 +272,7 @@
  */
 static inline uint32_t ring_buf_size_get(const struct ring_buf *buf)
 {
-    /* MASKED - implement this function */
+	return buf->put.head - buf->get.tail;
 }
 
